difference

public long difference(int field,
                       IBDCalendar other)
determines the difference between two IBDCalendar objects

Parameters:
field - the time field. These are inherited (ultimately) from IBDCalendar. Valid values are:
  • YEAR returns the number of years, 1/1/2001 - 12/31/2000 = 1 year.
  • MONTH returns the number of months, 2/1/2001 - 1/31/2001 = 1 month.
  • WEEK_OF_YEAR, WEEK_OF_MONTH, DAY_OF_WEEK_IN_MONTH returns the number of weeks between dates.
  • DATE, DAY_OF_YEAR, DAY_OF_WEEK returns the number of days between dates.
  • HOUR, HOUR_OF_DAY returns the number of hours between dates.
  • MINUTE returns the number of minutes between dates.
  • SECOND returns the number of seconds between dates.
  • MILLISECOND returns the number of milliseconds between dates.
    other - the other IBDCalendar
    Returns:
    long Time difference between IBDCalendar objedts
    Throws:
    java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an unknown field is given.

toJulian

public int toJulian()
Returns:
The Julian day number that begins at noon of this day Positive year signifies A.D., negative year B.C. Remember that the year after 1 B.C. was 1 A.D. A convenient reference point is that May 23, 1968 noon is Julian day 2440000. Julian day 0 is a Monday. This algorithm is from Press et al., Numerical Recipes in C, 2nd ed., Cambridge University Press 1992
